                    <span>Roth's latest book is based on a clever and interesting idea.  However several things contribute to my disappointment with this novel.  Philip Roth intrudes into the novel by being the principal character...Philip as a small boy growing up in Newark and his family ...and this device adds nothing and includes a lot of information which is, frankly, boring!
<br /> Secondly, the plot is totally unbelievable..not because Fascism couldn't happen here, but because the plot line and writing are
<br />simply not convincing.</span>
                  
              
